WorkItem.Description:
Does the _Layout property serve the same purpose as WebPageBase.Layout in MVC? If so, then shouldn't it be named without the underscore prefix?
 
There is a convention of the default layout being _Layout.cshtml (and prefixing layouts and partials with an underscore, in general). Is this just a carryover from this pattern?
 
I only suggest this because
 
    @{
        _Layout = "_Layout.cshtml";
    }
 
looks a little strange.
